descript.abstract: Census 2000 basic demographic data by tract. Includes a combination of SF1 and SF3 data including age, race, ethnicity, poverty, education, immigrant status, disabilities, households, and vehicles.
descript.supplinf:
Created by joining all the relevant files and deleting fields not wanted. Note that there are a number of fields used to created percentages, i.e. AGE25UP, AGE16UP, HUNITS. The data for these fields may come from either SF1 or SF3 files. At the tract level, there may be variations in total populations on the two files. These differences are small and can be ignored.
Census boundaries updated 12/2007 to those provided by Department of City Planning that were modified to fit the New York City base map.
